node.text:
Part 1 of 3 new brisket videos on our YouTube channel comparing different cook methods. We trimmed & seasoned 6 @44farms the same way and smoked them at 250° in the @mill.scale. 

I’m joined by my buddies @zavalasbarbecue & @jirby_bbq of @goldeesbbq to drop some knowledge and have an unbiased taste test at the end. We hope you enjoy this fun new series!

#MeatChurch #TexasBBQ #Brisket #44Farms #MillScale 📷: @katepraslickaphoto

node.title: Smoking Brisket wrapped in foil vs. Smoking Brisket wrapped in butcher pape

#MeatChurch

I made a March Madness bet with Troy (@alabamambb vs. @uclambb) and had to pay up my loss last night. I gladly cooked for his family + his close friends that he played football with at UCLA. I can’t say enough good things about Troy & his friends. We even got to hear our buddy @stevehelmsband play. Thank you for the hospitality, the jersey that’s headed to @meatchurchbbqsupply and the opportunity Troy!!

node.text:
Where does the time go? Our littles 1st day back to school today. Sam is going into 3rd grade and Ava Belle is going into 5th grade in her last year at Wilemon STEAM Academy. 

We are so ready for some structure again, so we’re happy they are back with their friends and we can all get back into our routines. I’m most excited that I can actually go eat lunch with them again. At least for now anyway.

We hope everyone has a great and healthy school year!

#MeatChurch #YETI

Pure Texas supper for @traciepittman & I tonight. Prime filet from @heb seasoned with our Holy Cow. Sous Vide in the @anovaculinary 90 @ 129°. Seared in hot cast iron 1 min per side for me & 2 min per side for the wife. Rested with Tuscan Herb butter also from @heb. Paired with @augustavinwinery Sagrantino from one of our favorite Texas wineries in Fredericksburg. This hit the spot!
